<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI MAYOR ANNOUNCES HAKKA CULTURE PROMOTION
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Feb. 3 (CNA) 02/03/07  17:40:39 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
Taipei Mayor Hau Lung-bin announced Saturday that the city
government will promote Hakka culture as one of the city's
marketing strengths.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the assembly of the World Hakka Women's Association,
Hau praised Hakka women for their "excellent abilities in the
household and career fields," adding that he is impressed by his
sister-in-law, who is "a diligent and competent Hakka woman."
</P>
<P>
Hau said the city government will focus its promotional efforts
on Hakka people's family concept, patriotism and diligence.
</P>
<P>
Tzeng Li-ching, president of the association, said the
association will organize a creative workshop on Hakka culture to
work on projects related to cultural exchange and economic
development.
</P>
